{"id": "EUVD-2022-54842", "enisaUuid": "b9e080fe-4097-3184-b2ad-ab6b2dc02789", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nwatchdog: rzg2l_wdt: Fix 32bit overflow issue\n\nThe value of timer_cycle_us can be 0 due to 32bit overflow.\nFor eg:- If we assign the counter value \"0xfff\" for computing\nmaxval.\n\nThis patch fixes this issue by appending ULL to 1024, so that\nit is promoted to 64bit.\n\nThis patch also fixes the warning message, 'watchdog: Invalid min and\nmax timeout values, resetting to 0!'.", "datePublished": "2025-02-26T02:11:21", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:46:51", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e07b9fa0dc32b492de85528caaf9f0c605d8424f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b95a47667d34e76c2c9013f8e3b1e5039a5a0b76", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ea2949df22a533cdf75e4583c00b1ce94cd5a83b"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49387"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "06a6501e-2fcb-34a5-849b-21c8f0008f91", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2cbc5cd0b55fa2310cc557c77b0665f5e00272de <ea2949df22a533cdf75e4583c00b1ce94cd5a83b"}, {"id": "14cff7db-7d61-3baf-98f1-f2a3ee2ccd33", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2cbc5cd0b55fa2310cc557c77b0665f5e00272de <e07b9fa0dc32b492de85528caaf9f0c605d8424f"}, {"id": "25a61f58-df5d-3c82-bbff-60c1cd08f0c0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "48d3b8aa-5f41-3b5b-9de6-e11ba2a9d2f2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19"}, {"id": "51ce0fe7-ef3d-3cdd-a11d-12f4fdd6a5b8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2cbc5cd0b55fa2310cc557c77b0665f5e00272de <b95a47667d34e76c2c9013f8e3b1e5039a5a0b76"}, {"id": "688c6eed-e275-3f79-bbea-f54ea55b6ea6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18.4"}, {"id": "840adafb-e59b-3b48-b8d1-a7704a434ed